    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith the *Tree-sitter* `ssh_config` syntax, I'm unable to disable spellcheck for any node.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nRun `nvim --clean -u init.lua` for:\n\n```lua\nload(vim.fn.system('curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/folke/lazy.nvim/main/bootstrap.lua'))()\n\nrequire('lazy.minit').repro({\n  spec = {\n    'nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n    config = function() require('nvim-treesitter').install({ 'ssh_config' }) end,\n  },\n})\n\nvim.opt.spell = true\n```\n\nMark a file with the `sshconfig` filetype. Add:\n\n```\nHost *\n    PasswordAuthentication no\n```\n\nHere `PasswordAuthentication` will be marked as having a typo.\n\nThe following in `:EditQuery` does not remove the spellcheck:\n\n```query\n(host_declaration) @nospell\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe spellcheck is removed.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A as this is Tree-sitter\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nSystem package manager",
