            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I'm not sure this bug is valid. With this init file, treesitter is not active when I open the buffer\n\n```\n[~/Documents/code/neovim] nick@fry$ cat minit.lua \nload(vim.fn.system('curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/folke/lazy.nvim/main/bootstrap.lua'))()\n\nrequire('lazy.minit').repro({\n  spec = {\n    'nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n    config = function()\n      require('nvim-treesitter').install({ 'ssh_config' })\n    end,\n  },\n})\n\nvim.opt.spell = true\n[~/Documents/code/neovim] nick@fry$ VIMRUNTIME=./runtime  build/bin/nvim -u minit.lua sshconfig\n```\nthen\n```\n:lua =vim.treesitter.highlighter.active[vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()]\nnil\n```\n\nRunning `:lua vim.treesitter.start()` immediately resolves the spellchecking problem on `PasswordAuthentication`\n\n<img width=\"313\" height=\"74\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/136c3881-10e6-49fc-9481-1a034ca35478\" />\n\nTested on both `master` and `0.12.1`",
